Package: cgvR
Type: Package
Title: Interactive 3D Visualization of Large Cayley Graphs via Vulkan
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Yuri", "Baramykov",
        email = "lbsbmsu@mail.ru",
        role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Cyrille", "Rossant",
        role = c("ctb", "cph"),
        comment = "Author of the Datoviz library")
    )
Description: Interactive 3D visualization of very large Cayley graphs using
    Vulkan-based rendering via the 'Datoviz' library. Renders graph neighborhoods
    on the fly within a configurable visibility zone (e.g. 10 moves from current
    node), enabling smooth navigation over graphs too large to display entirely.
    Supports flying camera, dynamic node/edge rendering, path highlighting, and
    multiple 3D layout algorithms. Uses 'cayleyR' for graph operations and
    Vulkan GPU drivers from 'ggmlR' for high-performance rendering.
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports:
    Rcpp
LinkingTo:
    Rcpp
Suggests:
    cayleyR,
    ggmlR,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
